Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The building is located near the hub of Fort Collins in Prospect East Business Park. Centrally located three miles from downtown Fort Collins and under two miles from I-25, it provides easy connectivity to Denver and DIA. The park is conveniently located near bike and pedestrian trails that wind through the business park to downtown Fort Collins and beyond. 3405 S. Timberline Road is located in the Timberline Corridor in Fort Collins, Colorado. Timberline Corridor has become one of the major office areas of choice in east Fort Collins.
The building is located just north of the Horsetooth/Timberline intersection and is just one mile from Harmony Road, the southern entry to Fort Collins from I-25. Convenient to bike trails, shopping, restaurants and lodging with Denver and DIA just an hour away. The building has ample parking and can accommodate almost any digital need.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Class A Large Office Building For Lease

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
Nestled alongside the Cache La Poudre River at the foothills of the Rocky Mountains, Fort Collins is home to approximately 167,830 residents as of 2019. Colorado State University is the city’s largest employer and is Colorado’s second largest public university, enrolling 25,000 students each academic year.
Fort Collins is the business center of Northern Colorado. It is the area’s center for government, retail trade, the arts, health care, education, and employment with the region’s largest and best educated workforce.
A blend of innovative manufacturing and high tech firms, an educated population, research facilities, and a first-rate research university that emphasizes commercialization of research makes Fort Collins one of the nation’s most innovative and entrepreneurial communities.
